Others: The Houston Rockets won against the San Antonio Spurs with a score of 127-100.
Fred VanVleet had a major game with 21 points, 7 rebounds, and 10 assists.
Alperen Sengun was extremely efficient with 16 points, 5 rebounds, 4 assists, 1 steal, and 2 blocks in just 24 minutes.
The Rockets shot 56.3% from the field and 37.0% from deep.
The Rockets are now on a two-game winning streak.
The Rockets will play the Oklahoma City Thunder tomorrow with serious momentum.
